<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="437" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,995,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,995,1019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Very small (3.0- 
<quantity box="[447,534,995,1019]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
), suboval, black-bronze species (
<figureCitation box="[888,954,995,1019]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (♂, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (♂, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♂, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (♂, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); elytra suboval with small, blue-green postscutellar stripe, frons very slightly convex, lateroposterior pronotal depressions very often with golden green tinge; parameres strongly constricted at apical third, median lobe sharply pointed (
<figureCitation box="[469,547,1091,1115]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="7.[113,152,1427,1446]" captionTargetBox="[113,1086,219,1277]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[113,1088,219,1278]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figs. 7–14. 7–9 – Habitus. 7 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Palawan); 8 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype (♂, 3.6 mm, Sibuyan); 9 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., allotype (♀, 3.9 mm, Luzon). 10–14 – Aedeagi (not in the scale). 10 – A. (H.) palawanensis sp. nov., holotype; 11 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, Mindoro; 12 – A. (H.) philippinensis sp. nov., holotype; 13 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, Luzon, Abra province; 14 – A. (H.) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype, Negros." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331373" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331373/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
). Sexual dimorphism nearly absent: the female differs from the male only by somewhat stouter body and by nearly parallel anterior two thirds of elytra which nearly completely cover the abdomen (elytra of male more sphenoidal, not completely covering abdomen) – see 
<figureCitation box="[550,652,1187,1211]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (♂, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (♂, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♂, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (♂, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Figs. 3, 6</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,995,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,402,1219,1243]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": BILY" authorityYear="1990" box="[408,843,1219,1244]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[408,504,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Anthaxia</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[520,667,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[683,843,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1900" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weyersi" subGenus="Anthaxia">
<emphasis box="[983,1006,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1021,1117,1221,1244]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Anthaxia</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[151,232,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">weyersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[248,357,1251,1275]" name="Indonesia" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[368,460,1251,1275]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[471,520,1251,1275]" country="Indonesia" name="Jawa Timur" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Java</collectingRegion>
) which differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": BILY" authorityYear="1990" box="[745,987,1251,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[745,768,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[784,811,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[827,987,1253,1276]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only weakly by the characters distinguishing both subgenera (well-expressed only in males), by the elytral epipleura reaching only the apical, rounded part of the elytra, by the lighter colouration, by the more sphenoidal body and by the form of the median lobe, which is slender and more pointed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": BILY" authorityYear="1990" box="[265,505,1379,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mindanaoensis" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[265,289,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[304,330,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">H.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[345,505,1381,1404]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">mindanaoensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="437" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1127,995,1563]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,1411,1435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the female 
<typeStatus box="[407,500,1411,1435]" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">holotype</typeStatus>
(see 
<figureCitation box="[553,612,1411,1435]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="6.[151,190,1282,1301]" captionTargetBox="[151,1126,221,1260]" captionTargetId="figure-11@6.[151,1126,219,1262]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figs. 1–6. Habitus. 1 – Anthaxia (Haplanthaxia) attenuata Fisher, 1922, holotype (♂, 4.0 mm, Negros); 2 – A. (H.) boettcheri Obenberger, 1928, lectotype (♂, 5.0 mm, Luzon); 3 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis Fisher, 1922, holotype (♀, 3.5 mm, Mindanao); 4 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♂, 3.9 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 5 – A. (H.) boettcheri (♀, 4.7 mm, Luzon, Abra province); 6 – A. (H.) mindanaoensis (♂, 3.5 mm, Mindoro)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5331369" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5331369/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) the elytra completely cover the abdomen, which was the main reason for attributing this species to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kerremans" authorityYear="1900" box="[742,903,1443,1468]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="weyersi" subGenus="Anthaxia">
<emphasis box="[742,766,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[782,806,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">A.</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[822,903,1445,1468]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">weyersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group (
<bibRefCitation author="BILY S." pageId="4" pageNumber="437" pagination="128 - 140" refId="ref5568" refString="BILY S. 1990: A revision of Anthaxia (Anthaxia) weyersi, species-group from South-East Asia (Coleoptera, Buprestidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca 87: 128 - 140." type="journal article" year="1990">BÍLÝ 1990</bibRefCitation>
). As a matter of fact, all members of this species-group are very close to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1911" box="[151,298,1509,1532]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="437" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Haplanthaxia">
<emphasis box="[151,298,1509,1532]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="437">Haplanthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
